Am Application Context Component is a Stealth EA concept representing a view of application data that maps directly to specific user screens or information exchanges within an application. Application context components aren't just database tables - they're architectural artefacts that document how data is persisted in the context of actual user interactions.

The key insight: an application context component answers "what data supports this specific user interaction in this specific application?" This linkage is what makes [[Data Provenance]] actionable - when data looks wrong, you can trace it back to the screen where someone entered it.

